message.content:
The output improved with the grouped layout but the weight transposition is still wrong. TF conv1d stores weights as [in, out] - I need to fix the weight indexing to use [in, out] format.

{
  "analysis": "The grouped layout with TF-alphabetical order gave alternating tokens (partial success). Need to fix weight matrix indexing from [out,in] to [in,out] (TF conv1d format). Also need to revert gamma+1 back to just gamma since that made things worse.",
  "plan": "Fix weight indexing to use [in,out] format (aw[i*3*C+j], ow[i*C+j], fw[i*F+j], pw[i*C+j]) and keep gamma (no +1).",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i '42s/(g\\[i\\]+1)/g[i]/' /app/gpt2.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i 's/xn\\[t\\*C+i\\]\\*aw\\[j\\*C+i\\]/xn[t*C+i]*aw[i*3*C+j]/' /app/gpt2.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i 's/ao\\[t\\*C+i\\]\\*ow\\[j\\*C+i\\]/ao[t*C+i]*ow[i*C+j]/' /app/gpt2.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i 's/xn\\[t\\*C+i\\]\\*fw\\[j\\*C+i\\]/xn[t*C+i]*fw[i*F+j]/' /app/gpt2.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i 's/ff\\[t\\*F+i\\]\\*pw\\[j\\*F+i\\]/ff[t*F+i]*pw[i*C+j]/' /app/gpt2.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep '\\*aw\\|\\*ow\\|\\*fw\\|\\*pw' /app/gpt2.c | head -8\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "gcc -O3 -o /app/a.out /app/gpt2.c -lm 2>&1 | grep error; /app/a.out gpt2-124M.ckpt vocab.bpe \"The meaning of life is\" 2>&1 | tail -1\n",
      "duration": 60.0
    }
  ]
}
